WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:05.480 --> 00:00:17.520
As we near the end of our presentation, let’s review what we’ve learned with we consider to be the key points to safe food handling known as the Food Worker Top 10.

00:00:18.660 --> 00:00:24.740
First off, Only work when you are healthy - if you are sick don’t work with food.

00:00:25.120 --> 00:00:28.600
Second, Wash your hands thoroughly and often

00:00:28.960 --> 00:00:34.340
Number three - Don’t touch ready-to-eat foods with your bare hands

00:00:35.020 --> 00:00:44.440
Four, Keep food Hot (135 degrees F) or Cold (41 degrees F)

00:00:46.020 --> 00:00:50.720
Five -  Cook foods to proper temperatures before serving

00:00:51.280 --> 00:00:56.100
Six - Cool Hot food as quickly as possible.

00:00:56.280 --> 00:01:00.400
Improper cooling is a leading contributor to foodborne illness

00:01:02.340 --> 00:01:06.380
Seven - Keep raw meat away from other foods.

00:01:07.300 --> 00:01:16.080
Eighth on the list, Always follow these four steps in order: Wash – Rinse – Sanitize – Air Dry.

00:01:16.440 --> 00:01:22.420
Next, remember to keep food prep area and utensils clean and sanitized.

00:01:22.880 --> 00:01:29.520
And last but not least, always ask your Person-In-Charge any questions you have on food safety.

00:01:30.120 --> 00:01:35.700
Thanks for joining us, and remember to be safe, it saves lives!

